cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper deals with the problem of crowd counting in images, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper proposes a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) based density estimation approach, which involves training a deep learning model to predict density maps. This suggests that the paper could also belong to the sub-categories cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves the use of multi-stage extensions to improve the accuracy of the predictions, which could fall under the sub-category cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper involves the use of iterative methods to generate high resolution density maps, which could also fall under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
